dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents addresses for Vernon County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Vernon_Addresses_2014.gdb.[This data set consists of digital map files containing addressing or site access information obtained predominantly by lab work. Features contained in the data set include all site access points countywide and associated attributes. Site access points sometimes are referred to as addresses, however these data typically represent the intersection of the public road right of way and the private entrance to the property. In the absence of a developed access feature the point represents the location of a line from the primary structure perpendicular to the public road right of way.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The site access feature class provides a digital representation of all addresses or site access points within Vernon County and is to be used in conjunction with developed digital road centerline, building, and driveway feature classes. The site access feature class was intended to be used to enhance addressing information within the County.]
